definitions: constituting number five in a sequence; 5th

examples.text: her mother had just given birth to another child, her fifth

definitions: each of five equal parts into which something is or may be divided.
shortDefinitions: each of five equal parts into which thing is divided

definitions: the fifth finisher or position in a race or competition
shortDefinitions: fifth finisher or position in race

definitions: (in some vehicles) the fifth (and typically highest) in a sequence of gears

examples.text: in my panic I changed from third to fifth

definitions: fifthly (used to introduce a fifth point or reason)

examples.text: fourth, it can aid the process of life review, and fifth, it is an enjoyable and stimulating experience

definitions: an interval spanning five consecutive notes in a diatonic scale, in particular (also perfect fifth) an interval of three whole steps and a half step (e.g., C to G)
shortDefinitions: interval spanning five consecutive notes in diatonic scale

definitions: the note which is higher by a fifth than the root of a diatonic scale.
shortDefinitions: note higher by such an interval than root of diatonic scale

definitions: a fifth of a gallon, as a measure of liquor, or a bottle of this capacity
the fifth grade of a school.
